       Fine Grain Service Monitoring System is a scalable, flexible infrastructure, software, and application monitoring tool. It can be used to monitor a wide variety of software components that aren't typically
       supported by vendors. FGSMS provides available and performance monitoring through agents which periodically report back to the server 
       where data is stored, aggregated and further processed. Each software component that is monitored is assigned a service policy, which defines what type of thing is being monitored, who owns it, who can access it and many more 
       settings. Each service policy can also define a number Service Level Agreements, enabling service owners and consumers to track its performance. When SLA rules are triggered, a number of actions can occur, such as 
       sending an email or sending WSDM alerts via JMS, AMQP, WSN.<Br><br>
       FGSMS is scalable. Through database clusters and redundant, load balanced Jboss servers, FGSMS can monitor entire infrastructures, 24-7-365.<br><br>
       This is just a small sample of the features FGSMS provides. Feel free to browse the help section for more information.
       
       
